svg.title: Norway’s legal biofuel minimum requirement for road transport

g.text: Norway’s legal biofuel minimum requirement for road transport

text.tspan: Advanced biofuels are those that are unlikely to lead
indirectly to deforestation or compete with food production.
So-called 'advanced' biofuels have a separate minimum
requirement, and during 2019-2022 these counted for double
to encourage their supply. From 2023 only advanced
biofuels in excess of the requirement count double.
